                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-15T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 15, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Your 103 and 105, June 13 and 14.<note n="55" xml:id="d1012fn1">Telegram No.
                        105, June 14, not printed.</note> Announcement in general terms of quota
                    restrictions on schedule articles and duty changes was issued by the Department
                    this morning.<note n="56" xml:id="d1012fn2">Department of State <hi
                            rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 15, 1940, p. 667.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0882" n="870" xml:id="pg_870"/>
                <p>Details will be published by Commerce as soon as possible. Please telegraph
                    immediately data on items 900 and 1086<hi rend="italic">b</hi>, and inform us
                    whether statistics in your 103 are for 3 or 6 month quotas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
